Implement ticket dependency tracking via an optional chipper-dependencies file.

Format (one relationship per line):
  <slug> depends-on <slug>

Commands:
  chipper <id> depends-on <id>   Add a dependency relationship
  chipper <id> remove-dep <id>   Remove a dependency relationship
  chipper deps <id>              Show all dependencies for a ticket
  chipper blocking <id>          Show all tickets that depend on the given ticket

Behavior:
- chipper start warns if any of a ticket's dependencies are not yet done
- chipper sort can optionally factor dependencies into sort suggestions
  (a ticket should not be ranked above its dependencies)
- chipper list can show dependency status alongside each ticket
- The file is optional — its absence does not affect any other chipper behavior

This is a separate manifest file alongside chipper-slugs and chipper-queue,
keeping the core manifest format simple and dependencies opt-in.

Depends on: manifest-implementation, status-commands
